cxr_findings:
The cardiac silhouette is normal.
There is no radiographic evidence of pulmonary edema. Stable opacities in the right lung. A new focal opacity is now seen in the left mid lung field.
There is no pneumothorax or effusion visible.
cxr_impression: Stable right lung multifocal opacity with new opacity now seen in the left mid-lung field. These could represent chronic scarring or persistent lesions related to reported COVID-19 infection. Continued imaging followup is recommended in 3-6 months to exclude other etiologies and confirm stability.
